lopment around the world for capacity building events. KDLC was equipped with state-of-the art Information Communication Technologies that includes an air conditioned and sound proof video conference room and multimedia laboratories with high speed internet. In 2012, the Implementation Committee mission assessed the KDLC Monitoring and Evaluation (in full) system and was generally gleaned as reliable and appropriate for the types of data KDLC was collecting. Assessment [of the 2008 -2011] specifically gleaned that KDLC had successfully offered over 364 capacity development training events of which 80 are Multimedia; 271 video conferences; and 13 face-to-face events. These skill development and capacity building programs, addressed learning programs such as: Financial Management Micro-Finance Electronic Records Management Leadership Dynamics for Senior Women Managers Combating Corruption in Procurement Fraud Investigation, Detection and Prevention Strategic Environment Assessment Development Policy; and Project Monitoring &amp; Evaluation. When the Kenya School of Government&nbsp;Act became effective on July 1st 2012, KDLC [now eLDi] joined GTIs and KIA to form the School.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":6086,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[126,118],"tags":[],"views":3592,"post_mailing_queue_ids":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/6085"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=6085"}],"version-history":[{"count":5,"href":"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/6085\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":6093,"href":"https:\/\/ksg.ac.ke\/